This paper is primarily focused on natural language understanding and classification tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization of performance characteristics such as model size and inference time, which could also place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of BERT, a popular model for natural language understanding, suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also mentions experimental evaluation on the standard GLUE benchmark, which involves tasks such as sentiment analysis and textual entailment, indicating a possible connection to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel method for improving inference time, which could potentially fall under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
